---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout>
    <section style="padding-top: 60px; border-bottom: none;">
        <div class="container reading" style="max-width: var(--container);">
            <span class="tag sanskrit">॥ व्यवस्था कौशलम् ॥</span>
            <span class="tag">Operations</span>
            <h1>Business Systems &amp; <span class="highlight">Automation</span></h1>
            <p class="lead" style="max-width: 650px;">
                Make your operations scalable. Reduce friction, improve consistency, and create operational capacity through better processes and automation.
            </p>
            <div style="display: flex; gap: 1rem; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
                <span style="font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; font-size: 1.2rem; color: var(--accent);">Starting at ₹50,000</span>
                <span style="font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; font-size: 1.2rem; color: var(--text-muted);">|</span>
                <span style="font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; font-size: 1.2rem; color: var(--text-muted);">Timeline: 4–8 Weeks</span>
            </div>
            <p style="font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--text-muted); border-left: 2px solid var(--accent-dim); padding-left: 1rem;">
                Systems Audit Included — Every Business Systems & Automation engagement begins with a Systems Audit and Discovery Process to ensure implementation decisions are based on evidence rather than assumptions.
            </p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section style="padding-top: 40px; border-bottom: none;">
        <div class="container reading" style="max-width: var(--container);">
            <h2>A Business System Is More Than Software</h2>
            <p>Most operational problems are not caused by a lack of effort. They are caused by unclear processes, inconsistent execution, and unnecessary manual work.</p>
            <p>Leads are missed. Follow-ups are delayed. Tasks depend on memory instead of systems. Information becomes fragmented across tools. As a business grows, complexity grows with it.</p>
            <p>A Business System creates structure. Automation helps that structure operate consistently at scale. Instead of relying on manual coordination for every task, we design workflows that reduce friction, improve consistency, and create operational capacity.</p>

            <h2 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Common Problems</h2>
            <ul class="structural">
                <li>Leads are managed manually</li>
                <li>Follow-ups are inconsistent</li>
                <li>Client onboarding takes too much time</li>
                <li>Information is duplicated across multiple tools</li>
                <li>Team members follow different processes</li>
                <li>Reporting requires repetitive manual effort</li>
                <li>Operations depend heavily on specific individuals</li>
                <li>Growth is creating operational complexity</li>
            </ul>
            <p>If several of these problems sound familiar, the issue is often structural rather than operational.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section style="padding-top: 40px; border-bottom: none;">
        <div class="container reading" style="max-width: var(--container);">
            <h2>Who This Is For</h2>
            <p>This engagement is designed for:</p>
            <ul class="structural">
                <li>Service Businesses</li>
                <li>Agencies</li>
                <li>Consultants</li>
                <li>Founder-Led Businesses</li>
                <li>Professional Firms</li>
                <li>Coaches & Educators</li>
                <li>Small Growing Teams</li>
            </ul>
            <p>If your business relies heavily on manual processes, fragmented workflows, or repetitive administrative work, this engagement may be a good fit.</p>

            <h2 style="margin-top: 2rem;">What This Is Not</h2>
            <ul class="structural">
                <li>Custom software development</li>
                <li>SaaS application development</li>
                <li>Mobile app development</li>
                <li>Enterprise ERP implementation</li>
                <li>Cybersecurity consulting</li>
                <li>AI model development</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Business Systems & Automation focuses on operational clarity, workflow design, process improvement, and practical automation.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section style="padding-top: 40px; border-bottom: none;">
        <div class="container reading" style="max-width: var(--container);">
            <h2>What You'll Receive</h2>
            <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1.5rem; margin-top: 1rem;">
                <div style="background: var(--surface); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 12px; border: 1px solid var(--border);">
                    <h3 style="font-size: 1.1rem;">The Blueprint Layer</h3>
                    <ul style="list-style: none; color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.9rem;">
                        <li>• Workflow Audit</li>
                        <li>• Process Architecture</li>
                        <li>• Systems Architecture</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div style="background: var(--surface); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 12px; border: 1px solid var(--border);">
                    <h3 style="font-size: 1.1rem;">The Operational Layer</h3>
                    <ul style="list-style: none; color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.9rem;">
                        <li>• Lead Management System</li>
                        <li>• Client Onboarding System</li>
                        <li>• Service Delivery Framework</li>
                        <li>• Operations Playbook</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h2 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Example Systems</h2>
            <ul class="structural">
                <li>Lead Management Systems</li>
                <li>Client Onboarding Systems</li>
                <li>Service Delivery Systems</li>
                <li>Internal Operations Systems</li>
                <li>Reporting Systems</li>
                <li>Documentation Systems</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section style="padding-top: 40px; border-bottom: none;">
        <div class="container reading" style="max-width: var(--container);">
            <h2>How The Process Works</h2>
            <ol style="color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 2;">
                <li><strong style="color: var(--text);">Step 1 — Systems Audit:</strong> Every project begins with a Systems Audit and Discovery Process.</li>
                <li><strong style="color: var(--text);">Step 2 — Discovery & Planning:</strong> Operational bottlenecks, priorities, and constraints are clarified.</li>
                <li><strong style="color: var(--text);">Step 3 — Systems Design:</strong> Processes, workflows, and automation opportunities are developed.</li>
                <li><strong style="color: var(--text);">Step 4 — Implementation:</strong> Approved systems and workflows are implemented according to project scope.</li>
                <li><strong style="color: var(--text);">Step 5 — Documentation & Handover:</strong> Documentation, guidance, and implementation notes are delivered.</li>
            </ol>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section style="padding-top: 40px; border-bottom: none;">
        <div class="container reading" style="max-width: var(--container);">
            <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
            <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.5rem;">
                <div>
                    <h3 style="font-size: 1.1rem;">Do I need automation before working with you?</h3>
                    <p style="font-size: 0.95rem;">No. Many businesses first need process clarity before automation becomes useful.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h3 style="font-size: 1.1rem;">Can existing tools be used?</h3>
                    <p style="font-size: 0.95rem;">Yes. Whenever possible, existing tools are incorporated rather than replaced.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h3 style="font-size: 1.1rem;">Will automation replace people?</h3>
                    <p style="font-size: 0.95rem;">Usually not. The objective is reducing repetitive work, improving consistency, and creating operational capacity.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h3 style="font-size: 1.1rem;">What if my business has no documented processes?</h3>
                    <p style="font-size: 0.95rem;">That is common. Part of the engagement involves identifying, documenting, and improving those processes.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h3 style="font-size: 1.1rem;">Is every project accepted?</h3>
                    <p style="font-size: 0.95rem;">No. Projects are evaluated before engagement to ensure the goals, scope, and expected outcomes are an appropriate fit.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div style="margin-top: 2rem; background: var(--surface); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 12px; border: 1px solid var(--border);">
                <h2 style="font-size: 1.5rem;">Build On A Strong Foundation</h2>
                <p>Tools change. Volume grows. Teams expand. A well-designed business system helps operations remain stable, predictable, and scalable through those changes.</p>
                <p style="font-style: italic; color: var(--accent);">For qualifying projects, the audit investment is credited toward the project scope.</p>
                <a href="/work-with-aman/systems-audit" class="btn" style="margin-top: 1rem;">Request a Systems Audit</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</Layout>